meta {
  name: [APISIX] deny request - no Authorization header
  type: http
  seq: 9
}

docs {
  EXPECTED behaviour once the auth-zen APISIX plugin is implemented.

  The plugin should:
    1. Detect that no Authorization header (or other supported credential) is present.
    2. Reject the request immediately without calling the policy agent.
    3. Return HTTP 401 to the client.

  This tests the "no subject" edge case: the plugin cannot build an AuthZEN evaluation
  input without a subject identity, so authentication is required before authorisation.
}

get {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/anything
  body: none
}

headers {
  accept: application/json
}

tests {
  test("status is 401 - no credentials provided", function() {
    expect(res.getStatus()).to.equal(401);
  });
}
